## No AI Framework Usage Detected

This codebase does not import any known AI SDKs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google GenAI, LangChain, HuggingFace, etc.). The scanner checked {{ pkg.code_scan.file_count }} files across Python and JavaScript/TypeScript.

**What this means for EU AI Act compliance:**

- **Articles 9-15** (high-risk obligations including technical documentation, record-keeping, and transparency) **do not apply via the Annex III pathway** since no AI system components were detected.
- **Article 50** may still apply if your application presents AI-generated content to users (e.g., content from an external AI API called at runtime without an SDK import, or embedded AI widgets). Note: disclosure is not required where AI interaction is obvious from context (Article 50(1)).
- **GDPR** obligations apply independently if your application processes personal data.

**If you believe this is incorrect**, your codebase may use AI through:
- Runtime API calls without an SDK (fetch/HTTP to `api.openai.com`, `api.anthropic.com`, etc.)
- AI functionality provided by a platform or framework not yet in our detection patterns
- AI models loaded from files rather than imported as packages

Please [open an issue](https://github.com/BipinRimal314/ai-trace-auditor/issues) if your AI usage pattern was missed.

